  "en_notes_asad": [
    {
      "note_no": "1",
      "note": "The term al-falaq (\"the light of dawn\" or \"the rising dawn\") is often used tropically to describe \"the emergence of the truth after [a period of] uncertainty\" (Taj al-'Arus): hence, the appellation \"Sustainer of the rising dawn\" implies that God is the source of all cognition of truth, and that one's \"seeking refuge\" with Him is synonymous with striving after truth."
    }
